description: üá≤üáΩ Pozole Rojo | Soups So Good It Can Cure Any Sickness Ep. 3 INGREDIENTS: Pozole Rojo - 1 kg pork (ham hocks) - 1 kg pork shoulder - 5 red onions, chopped - 12 cloves garlic, minced - Enough pork stock to reach the top of the pot.  - Maiz blanco (hominy) - 200g chile guajillo/ancho, (deseeded and to taste) - 2 bay leaves Blending Mixtures: - 3 tbsp dried oregano - 1 tbsp cumin - 5-6 cloves of garlic - 1 red onion, roughly sliced  - Ladle your mixture inside the blender.  Toppings: - Corn tortilla - Cabbage, sliced  - Red radish, sliced  - Cilantro, chopped  - 1 lime INSTRUCTIONS: - Start by adding your ham hocks (pata cut) into a hot pot with oil. Let it sear for a few minutes before removing from the container. Then saute your garlic and onions until softened, and pour pork broth until it fills the pot and bring to a boil. - In the meantime, deseed chilis and add this into the mixture and season with salt and pepper. Let it simmer for an hour. - Place everything under ‚Äúblending mixture‚Äù into a heat-safe blender. Blend until smooth and add it back into the pot. - Add additional sliced pork and ham hocks to the mixture, along with hominy and a bayleaf to season. description: We were out for lunch at Texas Roadhouse‚Äîa simple outing, like so many others. But for those living with FND, there‚Äôs no such thing as ‚Äúsimple.‚Äù Marci had just stepped out of the truck and taken a few steps toward the restaurant. I looked back and immediately noticed something wasn‚Äôt right‚Äîshe wasn‚Äôt responding. As I walked over to her, her legs buckled beneath her. I stepped in, caught her, and helped guide her safely to a nearby bench before she could fall. Others around us asked if we needed help‚Äîand I truly appreciated their concern. I let them know we had it under control. This is part of our life with Functional Neurological Disorder. Episodes like these are unpredictable. They happen without warning.
